  <refsect2 id="method-ossoabookpresence--get-status">
    <title>abook.Presence.get_status</title>

<programlisting><methodsynopsis language="python">
    <methodname>get_status</methodname>
    <methodparam></methodparam>  </methodsynopsis></programlisting>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term>
      <listitem><simpara>a <link linkend="abook-presence-status-constants"><literal>Presence Status</literal></link></simpara></listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>Retreives the status of this instance. Note that the "status" property
  can be monitored by connecting to the <classname>gobject.GObject</classname>
  "notify" signal with "status" as detail, i.e. "notify::status".</para>
  </refsect2>


  <refsect2 id="method-ossoabookpresence--get-icon-name">
    <title>abook.Presence.get_icon_name</title>

<programlisting><methodsynopsis language="python">
    <methodname>get_icon_name</methodname>
    <methodparam></methodparam>  </methodsynopsis></programlisting>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term><emphasis>Returns</emphasis>&#160;:</term>
      <listitem><simpara>The icon name currently associated with this instance.</simpara></listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para>Retrieves the icon name associated with the current status of this instance.
  The icon name can be used to look up the appropriate icon to represent this instance until
  the "status" property changes.</para>
  </refsect2>


